public boolean canBePolymorphic()

Returns true if this method can participate in virtual dispatch. Returns true for non-private instance methods; false for static methods, private instance methods, and constructors.

isEmpty

public boolean isEmpty()
Returns true if this constructor does no real work. NOTE: this method does NOT account for any clinits that would be triggered if this constructor is the target of a new instance operation from an external class. TODO(scottb): make this method less expensive by computing in an external visitor.
